<subSubSection id="D3BE655FFFBA3F0BFF3A9800B041FA6A" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9B1B36D4FFBA3F0BFF3A9800B041FA6A" blockId="2.[173,660,194,1437]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="A9D0EAC6FFBA3F0BFF3A9800B00DFBA9" bold="true" box="[197,301,1097,1118]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="5CA44D57FFBA3F0BFEC49803B323FBA8" authorityName="Botero" authorityYear="2015" box="[315,515,1098,1119]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xylocaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="A9D0EAC6FFBA3F0BFEC49803B323FBA8" box="[315,515,1098,1119]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Xylocaris hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="5CA44D57FFBA3F0BFF52982DB031FB8E" authorityName="Dupont" authorityYear="1834" box="[173,273,1124,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xylocaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="A9D0EAC6FFBA3F0BFF52982DB031FB8E" box="[173,273,1124,1145]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">X. oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the anterior region of the pronotum with shallow punctures and short, sparse setae, the mesepisternum, mesosternum, lateral region of metasternum, and metepisternum with dense, whitish pubescence, the color pattern: head and ventral region brownish orange, pronotum and scutellum orange, pro- and mesofemora orange with brown apex and metafemora brown with orange base. In 
<taxonomicName id="5CA44D57FFBA3F0BFEFF9970B042FAB9" authorityName="Dupont" authorityYear="1834" box="[256,354,1336,1358]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xylocaris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="A9D0EAC6FFBA3F0BFEFF9970B02EFAB9" box="[256,270,1337,1358]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">X</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="A9D0EAC6FFBA3F0BFEE39970B042FAB9" box="[284,354,1337,1358]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">oculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the surface of the pronotum is smooth, the ventral region lacks dense pubescence, and the head, prothorax, scutellum, ventral surface, and legs are black.
</paragraph>
